31:24.580 --> 31:27.280
me and my family aren't exactly close.

31:27.320 --> 31:28.350
well, that explains

31:28.380 --> 31:30.180
why you haven't designated any of them

31:30.220 --> 31:32.550
as beneficiaries to your life-insurance policy.

31:34.450 --> 31:36.880
what life-insurance policy?

31:39.720 --> 31:41.380
that's not your signature?

31:43.620 --> 31:44.650
no.

31:44.680 --> 31:46.250
thank you.

31:54.180 --> 31:55.120
ladies.

31:55.150 --> 31:57.480
thank you so much for coming in.

31:57.520 --> 31:59.320
i would have come to you,

31:59.320 --> 32:00.320
but -- crazy day.

32:00.350 --> 32:03.680
any-old-how,i have copies for both of you

32:03.720 --> 32:06.680
of roy wilkinson's death certificate.

32:06.720 --> 32:08.950
you'll need this to collect the life-insurance policy

32:08.980 --> 32:09.980
that roy left you,

32:10.020 --> 32:12.050
and karen will need one for the mortuary.

32:12.080 --> 32:14.950
have you decided what kind of service you're gonna have yet?

32:14.980 --> 32:16.080
not yet.

32:16.120 --> 32:17.550
is it going to be like the one

32:17.580 --> 32:19.480
you arranged for jerry nemec?

32:19.520 --> 32:21.150
i'm sorry?

32:25.280 --> 32:26.320
oh, shoot.

32:26.350 --> 32:28.080
i forgot my glasses.

32:28.120 --> 32:29.850
i'll be right back.

32:43.920 --> 32:45.120
okay.

32:47.780 --> 32:49.220
karen: we have nothing to worry about.

32:49.250 --> 32:51.150
we didn't have anything to do with this.

32:52.620 --> 32:54.950
so, sergeant,you see how useful it is

32:54.980 --> 32:59.820
to observe a person's first reaction to information.

33:07.750 --> 33:10.250
ladies.

33:12.280 --> 33:14.050
they were here all along.

33:15.180 --> 33:17.150
sweetie,it only gets worse.

33:17.180 --> 33:18.680
oh,that's what i've heard.

33:21.520 --> 33:23.280
you both are so incredible.

33:23.320 --> 33:25.480
all the good you do for these men,

33:25.480 --> 33:26.480
it's not surprising

33:26.520 --> 33:29.380
that they'd want to do something nice in return.

33:29.420 --> 33:32.020
well, a good deed is its own reward.

33:32.050 --> 33:35.180
sure, but a good deed and a life-insurance policy is even better.

33:36.480 --> 33:38.450
it's such a coincidence

33:38.480 --> 33:42.020
that both roy and jerry died the exact same way --

33:42.050 --> 33:44.420
drunk and hit by a car.

33:44.450 --> 33:48.620
it's unfortunate that so many of these released criminals

33:48.650 --> 33:51.220
fall into the same destructive patterns of behavior.

33:54.280 --> 33:56.080
hold that thought.

33:59.450 --> 34:02.380
oh, mr. francis.thank you so much for waiting.

34:03.320 --> 34:05.180
excuse me one second.

34:15.050 --> 34:17.280
did you talk to him?

34:17.320 --> 34:19.350
no. why would i?

34:20.420 --> 34:23.650
chief, you haven't read them their rights.

34:23.679 --> 34:25.020
no.

34:25.050 --> 34:28.580
they haven't given me a reason to -- yet.

34:38.949 --> 34:40.550
thank you for your patience.

34:40.580 --> 34:42.650
i had to say goodbye to mr. francis,

34:42.679 --> 34:43.920
who i just interviewed.

34:43.949 --> 34:45.520
do you think that jim francis

34:45.550 --> 34:47.080
had something to do with roy's death?

34:47.120 --> 34:48.880
oh, i'm certain of it.

34:48.920 --> 34:50.050
and it's strange,you know?

34:50.060 --> 34:53.050
i mean about he and roy have so much in common

34:53.060 --> 34:56.050
exconvicts£¬no families£¬struggled with addiction

34:56.060 --> 34:59.050
and they both have life-insurance policies

34:59.060 --> 35:01.050
the only difference is

35:01.060 --> 35:04.050
jim francis doesn't have a car mark across his chest

35:04.060 --> 35:05.050
what?

35:05.060 --> 35:06.050
well don't you have to run him over

35:06.060 --> 35:08.050
before you can collect the life-insurance money?

35:08.060 --> 35:10.050
what is she saying patty?

35:11.060 --> 35:13.050
i will read you that

35:14.060 --> 35:17.050
roy wilkinson's life-insurance policy--$80,000

35:17.060 --> 35:19.050
beneficiary --patricia simmons.

35:19.060 --> 35:22.050
and roy had a second policy --$150,000.

35:22.060 --> 35:24.050
beneficiary -- karen silva.

35:24.060 --> 35:26.050
the new claim hasn't been made yet

35:26.060 --> 35:29.050
jerry nemec's policy--$80,000

35:29.080 --> 35:31.150
beneficiary --patricia simmons.

35:31.180 --> 35:33.680
and he had a second policy --$150,000.

35:33.720 --> 35:35.720
beneficiary -- karen silva.

35:35.750 --> 35:37.550
bill johnson,luther madison --

35:37.580 --> 35:39.380
four men in the past five years,

35:39.420 --> 35:42.550
all living at your facility,all with life-insurance policies

35:42.580 --> 35:44.950
naming one or both of you as beneficiaries.

35:44.980 --> 35:47.320
all from different companies,of course.

35:47.350 --> 35:49.650
and it doesn't take an expert to see

35:49.680 --> 35:52.850
that all of these policies are written in the same hand.

35:52.880 --> 35:54.750
no, no.you don't understand.

35:54.780 --> 35:56.580
there are no families to pay for it,

35:56.620 --> 35:58.320
the state won't pay for it,

35:58.350 --> 36:01.180
and it is not cheap to give a man a decent funeral.

36:01.220 --> 36:03.420
and we can't afford it on what we make.

36:03.450 --> 36:06.250
i-i'm a volunteer. all i've got is my social security.

36:06.280 --> 36:08.750
so, you identify the hardest cases...

36:08.780 --> 36:11.980
and we make arrangements --just in case.

36:12.020 --> 36:14.380
well, you've become awfully good at identifying men

36:14.420 --> 36:18.120
who are 366 days away from being run over in an alley,

36:18.150 --> 36:21.050
because that is the exact way that all of these men died

36:21.080 --> 36:23.480
one year after you take out a policy.

36:23.520 --> 36:26.120
coincidentally, one year is the same amount of time

36:26.150 --> 36:28.480
it takes for a life-insurance policy to vest.

36:28.520 --> 36:30.120
now...

36:30.150 --> 36:32.550
i know you killed roy wilkinson.

36:32.580 --> 36:36.150
my question is...

36:36.180 --> 36:40.050
why does jim francis only have one policy?

36:40.080 --> 36:43.080
why does only karen get to cash in on him?

36:46.820 --> 36:48.950
it says so right here.

36:52.650 --> 36:54.420
you greedy bitch!

36:54.450 --> 36:55.550
patty, shut up!

36:55.580 --> 36:57.520
you greedy hoo.

37:00.550 --> 37:01.580
not another word!

37:07.520 --> 37:09.620
not another word!

37:09.650 --> 37:10.920
you said we were done!

37:10.950 --> 37:12.350
i said shut your mouth!

37:12.380 --> 37:15.650
you both have the right to remain silent.

37:15.680 --> 37:17.580
sergeant, could you...

37:17.620 --> 37:19.120
anything you say

37:19.150 --> 37:21.020
can be used against you in a court of law.

37:21.050 --> 37:23.550
you have the right to an attorney.

37:23.580 --> 37:25.020
i'll get you!

37:25.050 --> 37:26.880
if you cannot afford an attorney,

37:26.920 --> 37:28.380
one will be appointed to you.

37:28.420 --> 37:30.020
i can afford an attorney!

37:30.050 --> 37:31.150
you got to be kidding me.

37:31.180 --> 37:32.550
-do you understand these rights? -yes!

37:32.580 --> 37:33.720
all right. come on.

37:33.750 --> 37:36.050
easy, easy!ladies, that's enough!

37:36.080 --> 37:38.220
come on! easy!aaah!

37:38.250 --> 37:40.250
calm down. sit down.

37:40.280 --> 37:41.580
these men were criminals!

37:41.620 --> 37:43.720
they were drunks!

37:43.750 --> 37:46.380
with free housing and three meals a day!

37:46.420 --> 37:49.450
and we were waiting on them,getting older by the minute!

37:49.480 --> 37:51.820
at the end of the week,i could hardly stand up!

37:51.850 --> 37:53.820
and you're worried about roy wilkinson?!

37:53.850 --> 37:56.480
no. i'm worried about your retirement plan.

37:56.520 --> 38:00.120
now, i'm gonna write one of you up for murder in the first degree

38:00.150 --> 38:01.920
and one of you as an accessory.

38:01.950 --> 38:03.280
whose name goes where?

38:13.120 --> 38:14.580
we got roy drunk.

38:14.620 --> 38:17.050
he didn't want to go to the bar at first.

38:17.080 --> 38:19.880
but you told him that one drink wouldn't hurt,

38:19.920 --> 38:22.280
and you gave him another and another

38:22.320 --> 38:25.350
until you could practically pour him into that car --

38:25.380 --> 38:26.580
jerry nemec's car.

38:26.620 --> 38:30.080
roy passed out in the backseat,just like jerry.

38:30.120 --> 38:31.720
just like all the others.

38:31.750 --> 38:34.980
but a man who can't move is heavy.

38:35.020 --> 38:37.980
so you put him on a blanket

38:38.020 --> 38:40.120
and you pulled him out of the car

38:40.150 --> 38:42.780
and dragged him into the middle of that alley?

38:42.820 --> 38:44.320
yes.

38:44.350 --> 38:46.150
you know, you're --

38:46.180 --> 38:48.850
you're making it sound a lot worse than it was.

38:50.850 --> 38:53.350
after we hit him,i just wanted to go home.

38:53.380 --> 38:56.520
but you stopped to make sure he was dead.

38:56.550 --> 38:57.920
was he?

38:57.950 --> 39:00.050
no.

39:00.080 --> 39:02.050
he was just moaning.

39:02.080 --> 39:04.380
karen pulled the car away.

39:04.420 --> 39:06.880
i thought we were leaving.i was so relieved.

39:06.920 --> 39:10.250
and then she drove around the block and she did it again!

39:12.250 --> 39:14.150
karen? anything?

39:14.180 --> 39:16.480
she's lying.

39:19.720 --> 39:21.250
that'll be up to a jury

39:21.280 --> 39:24.350
to decide which one of you is telling the truth.

39:24.380 --> 39:27.150
i got to say,i don't like your odds.

